WEBVTT

00:04.137 --> 00:07.740
[Theme music playing]

00:07.741 --> 00:17.116
♪♪

00:17.117 --> 00:24.490
♪♪

00:24.491 --> 00:26.459
♪♪

00:29.443 --> 00:30.877
Good evening.

00:30.878 --> 00:34.447
I'm Helen Mirren, and you're
watching "Documentary Now!"

00:34.448 --> 00:36.282
season 52.

00:36.283 --> 00:39.486
Now, what causes someone to start a cult?

00:39.487 --> 00:42.455
And what causes someone to join one?

00:42.456 --> 00:46.025
In 1980, a man known as Father Ra-Shawbard,

00:46.026 --> 00:50.230
and his followers descended
upon a small town in Oregon

00:50.231 --> 00:53.299
to build a utopian community.

00:53.300 --> 00:56.636
What followed is one of
the strangest stories

00:56.637 --> 00:59.606
in American law enforcement history.

00:59.607 --> 01:03.110
This is "Batshit Valley."

01:05.946 --> 01:11.217
♪♪

01:11.218 --> 01:13.586
Man: Even now, knowing what I know,

01:13.587 --> 01:17.090
I have no regrets about my time
as a Shawbardite.

01:17.091 --> 01:23.463
♪♪

01:23.464 --> 01:25.799
My only regret is that
Father Ra-Shawbard was born

01:25.800 --> 01:28.123
before the world was ready for his message.

01:28.162 --> 01:29.102
_

01:29.103 --> 01:34.140
♪♪

01:34.180 --> 01:35.875
Woman: Being with Father Ra-Shawbard

01:35.900 --> 01:40.146
was like having a wonderful dream.

01:40.147 --> 01:43.550
And when you wake up and tell
people about the dream,

01:43.551 --> 01:48.096
only then do you realize
how foolish it was.

01:48.121 --> 01:49.689
Woman: Chinook is named for

01:49.690 --> 01:51.691
the Indians who settled this land.

01:51.692 --> 01:55.495
They would never have let anyone
take it away from them, so...

01:55.520 --> 01:56.520
_

01:56.715 --> 01:58.832
why would we?

01:58.833 --> 02:02.836
♪♪

02:02.837 --> 02:05.188
It's easy to look back
and say we took it too far.

02:05.213 --> 02:05.715
_

02:05.739 --> 02:07.640
But when your town is under siege,

02:07.641 --> 02:10.676
you'll do anything you can to protect it.

02:10.678 --> 02:15.415
Woman: People always say if I had
been nicer to the townspeople,

02:15.416 --> 02:17.618
none of this
would have happened.

02:18.868 --> 02:19.868
Well,

02:19.908 --> 02:22.589
maybe I would have been nicer
to the townspeople

02:22.590 --> 02:25.391
had they not been so fat and stupid.

02:25.392 --> 02:35.068
♪♪

02:35.069 --> 02:44.577
♪♪

02:44.578 --> 02:54.254
♪♪

02:54.255 --> 03:03.930
♪♪

03:03.931 --> 03:10.923
Season 3, Episode 1
Sync and corrections FunnyFunk

03:13.073 --> 03:15.485
Man: Chinook, Oregon, is a quiet town,

03:15.510 --> 03:17.577
one not accustomed to visitors.

03:17.578 --> 03:19.846
So it was quite a surprise two weeks ago

03:19.847 --> 03:22.715
when strangers dressed in yellow and black

03:22.716 --> 03:25.451
started arriving by the busloads.

03:25.452 --> 03:29.782
♪♪

03:29.807 --> 03:31.774
They call themselves Shawbardites,

03:31.813 --> 03:33.432
and they are followers of this man,

03:33.457 --> 03:34.861
Father Ra-Shawbard,

03:34.862 --> 03:36.521
a self-proclaimed spiritual leader

03:36.546 --> 03:39.799
who is now calling Chinook home.

03:39.800 --> 03:42.402
Woman: The sign to the gate
at Shawbard Valley Ranch

03:42.427 --> 03:43.925
says, "Everyone welcome."

03:43.957 --> 03:46.139
And the days are filled with meditation,

03:46.140 --> 03:50.076
light stretching, and meals
prepared from their own garden.

03:50.077 --> 03:51.911
But here at the Shawbard Valley Ranch,

03:51.912 --> 03:54.380
the Shawbardites only eat the vegetables

03:54.381 --> 03:57.050
after the vegetables give permission.

03:57.051 --> 03:59.310
And it seems as though
we're here on a good day,

03:59.342 --> 04:04.123
as all of the vegetables have
okayed themselves for consumption.

04:04.124 --> 04:06.667
♪♪

04:06.698 --> 04:09.262
The whole thing sounded
pretty out there to me.

04:09.263 --> 04:13.151
But at that point, it wasn't
like they were bothering anyone.

04:13.183 --> 04:14.556
♪♪

04:14.581 --> 04:15.937
_

04:15.968 --> 04:17.207
Woman: It's strange to think

04:17.245 --> 04:20.555
how things could have been so different
without that sign.

04:20.581 --> 04:23.183
When I heard on the news
that they talk to food,

04:23.208 --> 04:25.493
I thought this would be the funniest sign.

04:25.518 --> 04:26.995
People seem to like it.

04:27.867 --> 04:31.334
It's been getting smiles
from a lot of my customers.

04:31.359 --> 04:33.421
Oh, that's lovely, yeah.

04:33.453 --> 04:35.937
- It's funny, though.
- Uh-huh.

04:35.962 --> 04:38.157
When I read about the sign
in the grocery store,

04:38.158 --> 04:41.307
I was very upset.
It was very disrespectful.

04:41.332 --> 04:43.496
[Echoing] Very disrespectful,
very disrespectful...

04:43.497 --> 04:47.834
I know they say that sign
on the apples just proved

04:47.835 --> 04:49.842
that we were dead-set
against them from the beginning,

04:49.867 --> 04:51.668
but, honestly,
I don't think any of us

04:51.693 --> 04:53.339
were upset that they were here.

04:53.340 --> 04:57.059
You know, we were just
wondering why they were here.

04:57.091 --> 05:04.528
♪♪

05:04.553 --> 05:08.988
Ra-Shawbard was my father.

05:08.989 --> 05:12.288
I had a biological father,
but he wanted me to have a job

05:12.313 --> 05:14.304
and take on responsibilities.

05:14.329 --> 05:16.963
He never understood me.

05:16.964 --> 05:20.033
But Father Ra-Shawbard did.

05:20.034 --> 05:23.903
He just wanted me to be free and happy.

05:23.904 --> 05:25.720
And isn't that what a father is supposed

05:25.745 --> 05:27.000
to want for his children?

05:27.025 --> 05:30.109
And that's why it was an honor
to give him the money

05:30.110 --> 05:33.713
my real father gave me when he died.

05:33.714 --> 05:36.920
I first saw Father Ra-Shawbard
in a newspaper ad.

05:36.945 --> 05:37.661
_

05:37.685 --> 05:40.126
Woman: The words on the ad were so simple,

05:40.151 --> 05:42.455
but so profound...

05:42.456 --> 05:46.025
"Purify. Elevate. Liberate."

05:46.026 --> 05:49.376
I called the number,
and they gave me an address to send $40

05:49.401 --> 05:52.165
for some tapes of Father speaking.

05:52.166 --> 05:53.993
I sent it in, and when it didn't arrive,

05:54.018 --> 05:56.736
I called back and they said they
didn't know what had happened,

05:56.737 --> 05:58.590
and I should try again.

05:58.615 --> 06:01.140
I sent more money, and the tapes came.

06:01.141 --> 06:04.004
Anyone who listened to those tapes...

06:04.029 --> 06:05.996
had their life changed.

06:06.021 --> 06:07.914
"There is the world we see,

06:07.915 --> 06:11.559
but there's also a second world
that we do not..."

06:11.584 --> 06:15.221
"How do we unlock the door
for that world?"

06:15.222 --> 06:20.021
"And if there's a second world,
could there be a third one?"

06:20.046 --> 06:21.808
"A fourth one?

06:21.833 --> 06:24.919
Could there be a sixth world?"

06:24.944 --> 06:27.867
I ordered a new tape every week.

06:27.868 --> 06:30.281
And on my 20th, I received an invitation to

06:30.306 --> 06:33.187
Shawbard Valley Ranch,
and I never looked back.

06:33.212 --> 06:42.949
♪♪

06:42.950 --> 06:46.640
♪ Babe, I want to tell you ♪

06:46.665 --> 06:47.783
Woman: By the second day,

06:47.808 --> 06:50.189
I had completely forgotten about my husband

06:50.190 --> 06:52.125
and two children that I left behind.

06:52.126 --> 06:55.833
♪ I fell in love with you ♪

06:55.858 --> 06:59.165
♪ Ooh ♪

06:59.166 --> 07:01.789
♪ In the air, we can fly ♪

07:01.814 --> 07:04.472
♪ In the sea, we can dive ♪

07:04.497 --> 07:10.309
♪ Together, we could get high ♪

07:10.310 --> 07:12.501
♪♪

07:12.526 --> 07:15.181
Ra-Shawbard: This is your home.

07:15.182 --> 07:19.144
But in order for it to truly be your home,

07:19.169 --> 07:23.673
you have to abandon all the trappings
of your former life.

07:23.698 --> 07:27.760
So I ask all of you to write down the names

07:27.761 --> 07:32.292
of your family members
that you are leaving behind...

07:32.332 --> 07:34.760
and put them in this basket.

07:34.785 --> 07:36.721
Along with their Social Security Number

07:36.752 --> 07:39.106
and their banking information.

07:40.633 --> 07:44.577
And then you will be free.

07:44.578 --> 07:48.107
♪ I fell in love with you ♪

07:48.132 --> 07:50.149
Man: We had created a paradise.

07:50.150 --> 07:52.685
♪ Fell in love with you ♪

07:52.686 --> 07:56.014
♪♪

07:56.039 --> 07:58.224
And I think we would still be there

07:58.225 --> 08:01.361
if it wasn't for those awful townspeople.

08:02.921 --> 08:09.596
♪♪

08:09.621 --> 08:12.905
Man: They'd have you believe
we started the ill will.

08:12.906 --> 08:17.645
But in the beginning, we actually tried
to engage with the Shawbardites.

08:17.670 --> 08:19.700
Woman: Well, I would argue
that we went out of our way

08:19.725 --> 08:21.247
to make them feel welcome.

08:21.248 --> 08:24.163
Oh, yeah, cover up that
bird's head, we don't need...

08:24.188 --> 08:25.161
_

08:25.185 --> 08:28.487
The only problem was
they were having these orgies.

08:28.488 --> 08:31.836
And, hey, I don't have
a problem with orgies.

08:31.861 --> 08:35.291
If that is your thing,
more power to you.

08:35.316 --> 08:37.418
But they were very loud.

08:37.443 --> 08:41.861
Well, we had to have a town
meeting to discuss the...

08:41.886 --> 08:44.203
orgies.

08:45.521 --> 08:47.751
It was decided that I would
go up to the ranch

08:47.776 --> 08:50.529
and see if I could convince them to...

08:50.554 --> 08:52.989
you know, at the very least,
close their windows.

08:53.014 --> 08:55.737
But it did not go well.

08:55.762 --> 08:57.776
Hello there. I'm Marge Middleton.

08:57.801 --> 08:59.126
I'm the Mayor of Chinook.

08:59.151 --> 09:01.785
Yes, we know who you are.

09:01.810 --> 09:04.156
Well, we just wanted
to formally welcome you.

09:04.157 --> 09:08.704
Is there something that we can
help you with, Marge Middleton?

09:08.729 --> 09:13.232
Their spokesperson was a woman
named Ra-Sharir,

09:13.233 --> 09:16.559
and she was not
an easy person to deal with.

09:16.584 --> 09:19.773
Well, it's about the orgies.

09:21.757 --> 09:23.934
And?

09:23.959 --> 09:27.092
I'm sorry, have I done
something to offend you?

09:27.117 --> 09:28.942
We saw your sign.

09:28.967 --> 09:30.188
What sign is that?

09:30.213 --> 09:33.252
The one in the grocery store.

09:33.253 --> 09:35.988
"We are happy to be here,
love, the apples."

09:35.989 --> 09:39.470
Gosh, that's just Pam doing her Pam thing.

09:39.495 --> 09:41.383
I hope you weren't offended by that.

09:41.408 --> 09:44.546
Oh, you will know when I am offended.

09:44.571 --> 09:48.030
You will know.

09:48.055 --> 09:50.903
Now, please disperse.
This is a private property.

09:50.928 --> 09:54.006
So, you know, we went home.

09:54.007 --> 09:58.685
♪♪

09:58.710 --> 10:01.210
You know, I think we would
have been willing to chlalk it up

10:01.241 --> 10:04.183
to different world views, but...

10:04.184 --> 10:06.385
that night, they installed a speaker system

10:06.386 --> 10:08.609
and hooked it up to the orgy room.

10:08.640 --> 10:13.192
[Amplified moaning]

10:13.193 --> 10:16.963
♪♪

10:16.964 --> 10:24.971
They used a lot of specific
words about body parts and...

10:24.972 --> 10:27.039
and where they wanted them put.

10:27.040 --> 10:31.343
♪♪

10:31.368 --> 10:35.247
The next morning,
I did what I had to do.

10:35.248 --> 10:40.454
I issued them a $100 fine for
violating the sound ordinance.

10:41.088 --> 10:42.922
Man: A lousy hundred bucks.

10:42.923 --> 10:46.225
They treated it like an act of war.

10:46.226 --> 10:48.694
It's only been a month,
but tensions are starting

10:48.695 --> 10:51.285
to rise between the town
of Chinook and the Shawbardites,

10:51.310 --> 10:53.731
who don't seem to want
to follow their rules.

10:53.756 --> 10:56.672
[Echoing]
This is not about sound.

10:56.704 --> 10:57.791
No!

10:57.816 --> 11:01.783
This is about one religion exerting power

11:01.808 --> 11:04.015
over another religion.

11:04.040 --> 11:08.237
Woman: Most of us were of the mind
that Ra-Sharir was overreacting.

11:08.262 --> 11:10.579
And, mercifully, Father agreed.

11:10.604 --> 11:14.820
We are not here to make enemies.

11:14.821 --> 11:16.789
We're here to make peace with ourself.

11:16.790 --> 11:20.139
The world has enough
aggression and escalation

11:20.164 --> 11:23.695
without us adding to it.

11:23.720 --> 11:25.226
Plus, I don't think we want people

11:25.251 --> 11:26.925
digging around in our thing.

11:26.950 --> 11:29.036
Do...

11:29.061 --> 11:30.814
What do you guys think?

11:30.839 --> 11:37.843
♪♪

11:37.844 --> 11:39.679
Well, she paid the fine.

11:39.704 --> 11:41.814
I came into my office
the next day to find

11:41.815 --> 11:46.385
$100 worth of pennies
spilled all over my desk.

11:46.386 --> 11:49.755
There was also a dead snake,
but it was just a little one.

11:49.756 --> 11:54.795
♪♪

11:59.733 --> 12:00.973
Man: Halloween.

12:01.013 --> 12:03.132
It's usually a night
where the town gets together

12:03.157 --> 12:04.804
for some spooks and scares.

12:04.805 --> 12:06.439
But tonight, the spooks and scares

12:06.440 --> 12:08.951
were a little too real as Ra-Sharir,

12:08.976 --> 12:10.443
a member of the Shawbardites,

12:10.468 --> 12:13.712
made it clear that when it comes
to judging carved pumpkins,

12:13.713 --> 12:16.364
Mayor Middleton
doesn't know jack...

12:16.389 --> 12:17.586
'o-lantern.

12:17.611 --> 12:22.466
It is my honor to announce that
this year's Pumpkin Patch Pal is

12:22.491 --> 12:24.256
Sally Walters!

12:24.257 --> 12:26.500
Congratulations.

12:26.525 --> 12:29.897
What?! What madness is this?

12:29.922 --> 12:31.964
Are you the Mayor of Stupid?

12:31.965 --> 12:34.317
Man: - Sit down.
- You sit down!

12:34.342 --> 12:35.901
All of you sit down.

12:35.902 --> 12:38.843
Nobody thinks that is the best pumpkin.

12:38.868 --> 12:39.858
No one!

12:39.883 --> 12:42.741
Give me one reason
why my pumpkin is not the winner!

12:42.742 --> 12:45.911
Now, I'll concede that Ra-Sharir
had a well-carved pumpkin,

12:45.912 --> 12:48.647
but it didn't seem right to award an adult

12:48.648 --> 12:51.526
for what was clearly a children's contest.

12:51.551 --> 12:53.052
Ra-Sharir, you're an adult.

12:53.053 --> 12:56.091
And this isn't a contest for adults.

12:56.116 --> 12:57.923
Where does it say that?

12:57.924 --> 13:01.282
Huh? Show me in the rules,
where does it say that?

13:01.307 --> 13:04.972
I demand to speak with someone.

13:04.997 --> 13:07.686
- You want to talk with someone?
- Yeah.

13:07.711 --> 13:09.527
I'll admit, I said something
I shouldn't have,

13:09.552 --> 13:11.519
but I was upset, and it just came out.

13:11.544 --> 13:14.067
Why don't you go talk to your vegetables.

13:14.092 --> 13:19.997
[Laughter]

13:20.022 --> 13:23.339
Man: There was no doubt
that Marge hit a nerve.

13:23.364 --> 13:25.918
We all assumed it was only a matter of time

13:25.919 --> 13:28.615
before Ra-Sharir retaliated.

13:28.640 --> 13:31.559
Man: A break-in last night
at the local paper here in Chinook,

13:31.584 --> 13:33.893
nothing stolen, nothing broken.

13:33.894 --> 13:36.128
But something added to today's paper...

13:36.129 --> 13:40.699
an obituary for the still very
alive Mayor Marge Middleton.

13:40.700 --> 13:43.169
There was no proof that Ra-Sharir did it.

13:43.170 --> 13:46.305
But it was definitely in her voice.

13:46.306 --> 13:49.308
♪♪

13:49.309 --> 13:53.212
"Today, Marge Middleton lost
her long battle with stupidity.

13:53.213 --> 13:56.086
She will not be remembered
by her friends and family,

13:56.111 --> 13:58.679
as they are too stupid to do so.

13:58.704 --> 14:03.949
Services will be held wherever
stupid people are buried."

14:03.974 --> 14:05.891
Man: Yeah, you had to give Marge credit.

14:05.892 --> 14:08.246
She kept her cool through the whole thing.

14:08.286 --> 14:10.429
Right up until the story went national.

14:10.454 --> 14:14.365
Tonight, a small town in Oregon
may lose its name,

14:14.390 --> 14:16.540
thanks to the efforts of newcomers

14:16.565 --> 14:20.039
who intend to use
the power of the ballot box.

14:20.040 --> 14:22.762
We are currently in the process
of registering our members

14:22.787 --> 14:25.547
to vote in the next municipal election.

14:25.572 --> 14:29.014
The first act of our majority
will be to give this town

14:29.015 --> 14:33.127
a name worthy
of its beautiful surroundings...

14:33.158 --> 14:36.508
"Ra-Shawbarda."

14:36.533 --> 14:39.158
Man: They had the votes.
There was no doubt.

14:39.159 --> 14:41.493
But Marge saw the writing on the wall,

14:41.494 --> 14:44.096
and God love her, she took action.

14:44.097 --> 14:46.956
We felt that for the next nine months,
there was a more fitting name.

14:46.981 --> 14:50.988
Man: For over 200 years, this small part
of Oregon has been known as Chinook.

14:51.013 --> 14:53.138
But today, it has a new name.

14:53.139 --> 14:57.353
When motorist enter town,
they will see this sign as they drive into

14:57.378 --> 14:59.414
Ra-Shawbard's Butthole.

14:59.454 --> 15:04.438
Woman: You heard me right, the new name
of the town is Ra-Shawbard's Butthole.

15:04.463 --> 15:07.019
I thought it was pretty funny.

15:07.020 --> 15:09.168
But I had never seen Ra-Sharir more angry.

15:09.200 --> 15:11.390
This is a sacrilege!

15:11.415 --> 15:14.628
This is the mockery of a holy man!

15:14.653 --> 15:18.406
A man of who every part is sacred,

15:18.431 --> 15:20.869
including his butthole,

15:20.894 --> 15:24.473
of which this town knows nothing.

15:24.498 --> 15:28.488
Father had already admonished
Ra-Sharir once, so we just assumed

15:28.513 --> 15:31.867
he would put his foot down
to stop her escalation.

15:31.892 --> 15:35.303
♪♪

15:35.328 --> 15:41.662
But this was when we started to realize,
something was...

15:41.687 --> 15:43.822
off with him.

15:43.823 --> 15:47.726
[Muttering indistinctly]

15:47.727 --> 15:51.273
♪♪

15:51.298 --> 15:53.527
Woman: He was always in a daze.

15:53.552 --> 15:56.302
And he seemed unable to walk.

15:56.303 --> 16:01.048
So his chair was attached to a motorized
wheelchair that brought him on stage.

16:01.073 --> 16:04.421
Man: This was when Ra-Sharir announced
that he had taken a vow of silence.

16:04.446 --> 16:07.278
Father will use his silence

16:07.303 --> 16:09.720
to contemplate solutions

16:09.745 --> 16:11.950
to what plagues this world.

16:11.975 --> 16:15.054
It's okay.

16:15.055 --> 16:18.157
It was such a trusting place
that I don't think it ever

16:18.158 --> 16:21.008
occurred to any of us
that his diminished state,

16:21.033 --> 16:23.362
followed by his vow of silence

16:23.363 --> 16:26.191
had been chemically induced by Ra-Sharir.

16:26.216 --> 16:31.338
♪♪

16:33.265 --> 16:35.940
Man: Ra-Sharir had always been
Father Shawbard's mouthpiece,

16:35.965 --> 16:38.744
but now she was taking
control of his checkbook.

16:38.745 --> 16:40.512
I always felt like we were using our money

16:40.513 --> 16:43.148
to make a better life for ourselves.

16:43.149 --> 16:45.718
But now she spent it
to make lives worse for others.

16:45.719 --> 16:47.653
Well, if the people of what
was formerly Chinook

16:47.654 --> 16:51.253
were looking for a reaction with
their name change, they got one.

16:51.278 --> 16:54.134
It seems that the Shawbardites
have been secretly purchasing

16:54.159 --> 16:55.912
all the land around the town

16:55.937 --> 16:57.904
and now have it encircled.

16:57.936 --> 17:00.599
Man: Heck, I tip my cap to their ingenuity.

17:00.600 --> 17:03.272
Buying up land is
the American Goddamn dream.

17:03.297 --> 17:06.238
But now they've installed
these speed bumps.

17:06.239 --> 17:10.516
So many speed bumps that at
500-feet worth to be exact.

17:10.540 --> 17:13.738
We decided to take the News 9 van
overthe speed bumps

17:13.762 --> 17:16.944
to give you an idea of what it feels like.

17:16.969 --> 17:18.643
Back to you, Bob.

17:18.667 --> 17:20.378
It was destroying our mufflers.

17:20.404 --> 17:22.521
And then to make matters worse,
the Shawbardites

17:22.547 --> 17:25.220
had secretly purchased
the town muffler shop

17:25.244 --> 17:28.426
and converted it into a green juice stand.

17:28.452 --> 17:31.854
Ra-Sharir: I think the people of this
town should see this as an opportunity.

17:31.879 --> 17:34.561
If your muffler shop is closed,
buy green juice.

17:34.586 --> 17:36.180
You'll be healthier and happier.

17:36.205 --> 17:37.894
You're a monster!

17:37.919 --> 17:39.626
When are you gonna leave us alone?

17:39.651 --> 17:42.967
Why don't you go back to your butthole!

17:42.992 --> 17:46.612
This is America. You cannot open
a juice bar in a muffler shop.

17:46.613 --> 17:50.682
I don't care who your god is,
you need permits.

17:50.683 --> 17:53.744
Man: They used to fix mufflers,
then they served juice.

17:53.775 --> 17:55.720
Then the juice was muffled.

17:55.745 --> 17:58.506
But have we heard the last of it?

17:58.531 --> 18:00.441
This is war.

18:00.466 --> 18:03.283
We figured war meant
she'd T.P. the grade school.

18:03.308 --> 18:10.806
♪♪

18:10.831 --> 18:14.482
Ra-Sharir: Advance! Positions.

18:14.507 --> 18:17.395
Man: We didn't think she'd go so far
as to arm themselves.

18:17.420 --> 18:19.037
Fire!

18:19.086 --> 18:24.589
[Gunfire]

18:24.614 --> 18:25.898
It was terrifying!

18:25.923 --> 18:27.589
Man: It was a scary time.

18:27.614 --> 18:30.322
The shooting range was very near
the room we had orgies in.

18:30.323 --> 18:32.524
And more than once,
a bullet came through the wall.

18:32.525 --> 18:34.690
It was clear that the only person

18:34.715 --> 18:38.848
who could stop Ra-Sharir was
Father Ra-Shawbard.

18:38.873 --> 18:41.500
But he was out of it.

18:41.501 --> 18:43.438
He was certain
that Ra-Sharir had been giving him

18:43.463 --> 18:45.471
a cocktail of Valium and barbiturates.

18:45.472 --> 18:47.707
He said he needed to speak
to the whole community,

18:47.732 --> 18:50.279
but he would need something
to get his energy back.

18:50.304 --> 18:51.739
_

18:51.764 --> 18:52.488
_

18:52.513 --> 18:54.200
_

18:54.557 --> 18:56.257
_

18:57.819 --> 18:59.451
It did surprise me that a man

18:59.452 --> 19:04.161
who spoke of the purity
of mind and soul had cocaine.

19:04.186 --> 19:07.392
A good deal of cocaine,
as it turns out, in his bedside drawer.

19:07.393 --> 19:08.961
Ra-Shawbard: Yeah, talky, talky, talky.

19:08.962 --> 19:10.083
Back back, baby back.

19:10.108 --> 19:12.645
They think I can't hear,
but I hear everything.

19:12.670 --> 19:15.100
I hear the mice think,
I hear the plugs conspiring,

19:15.101 --> 19:17.403
and I realize in my silence,
that I am not communing with God.

19:17.428 --> 19:22.277
I am God, and my power
will be challenged by no man and no mouse.

19:22.302 --> 19:27.256
Woman: In the state he was in, it was easy
for Ra-Sharir to manipulate him.

19:27.281 --> 19:29.982
This is wonderful news!

19:29.983 --> 19:34.753
I believe she convinced him
to prove that he was a god.

19:34.754 --> 19:37.356
Ra-Sharir: Today, Father Ra-Shawbard will

19:37.357 --> 19:39.127
prove his divinity

19:39.152 --> 19:43.293
by allowing an automobile
to harmlessly pass

19:43.318 --> 19:45.176
through his corporeal body.

19:45.201 --> 19:47.366
- Who?
- You, Father.

19:47.367 --> 19:49.501
Man: One of the Shawbardites
jumped in a car

19:49.502 --> 19:51.870
and barreled down towards
Father Ra-Shawbard,

19:51.871 --> 19:55.741
who was going to prove to us
that he was a god.

19:55.766 --> 20:01.647
I should have said something,
but I actually believed it might be true.

20:01.648 --> 20:05.670
And if it was, I wanted to see it.

20:05.695 --> 20:10.989
♪♪

20:10.990 --> 20:13.916
Where... Where are you going?

20:13.941 --> 20:17.771
Send someone to get my blue hat.

20:17.796 --> 20:19.831
I'm a little chilled.

20:19.832 --> 20:21.755
[Engine revving]

20:21.780 --> 20:23.692
Ra-Sharir?

20:23.717 --> 20:25.871
Oh, my God!

20:25.872 --> 20:31.252
♪♪

20:31.277 --> 20:32.455
_

20:32.480 --> 20:34.296
_

20:34.321 --> 20:35.719
_

20:35.744 --> 20:36.481
♪♪

20:36.482 --> 20:39.370
Woman: It was troubling
that he was asking for a hospital,

20:39.395 --> 20:42.902
as he had sworn off
the use of modern medicine.

20:42.927 --> 20:44.690
And then...

20:44.691 --> 20:49.329
he said the words that brought
our whole world crashing down.

20:49.590 --> 20:50.900
_

20:50.925 --> 20:51.835
_

20:51.860 --> 20:55.360
_

20:57.441 --> 20:59.845
And after we heard that...

20:59.870 --> 21:02.975
you are surprised with what happened next?

21:02.976 --> 21:06.472
♪♪

21:06.497 --> 21:08.679
♪ Got together ♪

21:08.703 --> 21:12.072
♪ Splendors of before ♪

21:12.073 --> 21:13.874
♪ When you go down ♪

21:13.875 --> 21:16.544
Breath is the answer to everything.

21:18.813 --> 21:20.376
Oh, yeah.

21:20.401 --> 21:22.949
Feel it?

21:22.950 --> 21:24.819
Look up to the sky.

21:27.221 --> 21:29.923
Let your body feel it.

21:29.924 --> 21:32.759
Oh, yes.

21:32.760 --> 21:33.960
Oh.

21:33.961 --> 21:36.963
Feeling it this morning.

21:36.964 --> 21:39.599
Body's saying thank you.

21:39.600 --> 21:41.336
Gracias.

21:44.138 --> 21:48.942
♪♪

21:48.943 --> 21:50.644
Ra-Sharir?

21:50.645 --> 21:53.081
Man: Oh, my God!

21:54.248 --> 21:59.188
Wayne: Listen, you idiots,
I work for the [echoing] FBI!

21:59.213 --> 22:01.561
And after we heard that...

22:01.586 --> 22:04.791
you are surprised with what happened next?

22:04.792 --> 22:11.895
Season 3, Episode 2
Sync and corrections FunnyFunk

22:11.920 --> 22:20.488
♪♪

22:20.513 --> 22:22.141
Doss: My name is Bill Doss.

22:22.142 --> 22:24.056
I'm former FBI.

22:24.081 --> 22:28.612
Wayne Delancey, A.K.A. Father Ra-Shawbard,
was my informant.

22:28.637 --> 22:31.676
_

22:31.701 --> 22:33.057
In the late '70s, I was assigned

22:33.082 --> 22:35.454
to the elite cult unit of the FBI.

22:35.455 --> 22:38.208
We had been formed
after the tragedy of Jonestown

22:38.233 --> 22:40.993
for the unique purpose
of stopping cult activity.

22:40.994 --> 22:42.740
_

22:42.765 --> 22:44.525
_

22:44.550 --> 22:47.136
I reached out to a colleague of mine...
Larry Cooper.

22:47.161 --> 22:48.976
Larry had been profiling serial killers.

22:49.001 --> 22:50.335
We're having drinks one night, and I said,

22:50.336 --> 22:52.670
"Larry, how the hell am I ever gonna know

22:52.671 --> 22:55.974
what a nut bag like Jim Jones is thinking?"

22:55.975 --> 22:58.209
Larry looks at me and says,

22:58.210 --> 23:00.516
"What if the nut bag worked for you?"

23:00.541 --> 23:02.914
The problem with profiling serial killers

23:02.915 --> 23:06.184
is that you can only do it
after they've killed a bunch of people.

23:06.185 --> 23:08.708
This way, we could learn what we need to

23:08.733 --> 23:10.105
and no one would get hurt.

23:10.130 --> 23:12.367
It was a hell of a plan...

23:12.392 --> 23:14.125
on paper.

23:14.126 --> 23:17.295
Doss: Our first order of business
was to find ourselves a front man.

23:17.296 --> 23:19.697
Someone had to run the cult, right?

23:19.698 --> 23:22.767
And then, like a gift from the gods,

23:22.768 --> 23:24.840
Paternius just falls into our lap.

23:24.865 --> 23:27.304
♪ Doo doo doo doo ♪

23:27.329 --> 23:30.808
♪ You know I'll be waiting on the corner ♪

23:30.809 --> 23:32.010
♪ Whoo-whoo ♪

23:32.011 --> 23:33.211
Paternius... real name

23:33.212 --> 23:35.279
Wayne Delancey...
had a health food store

23:35.304 --> 23:37.892
on Sunset Boulevard
that specialized in yogurt.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.972
He called the place Counter Culture.

23:39.997 --> 23:43.815
The place had a staff of about 20 girls,
not a bra between 'em.

23:43.847 --> 23:45.283
Cooper: The guy is raking it in.

23:45.308 --> 23:47.458
Buys a nice house in the hills,

23:47.459 --> 23:49.888
lives there with 50 or so of his followers.

23:49.913 --> 23:53.277
They call themselves Paternians.

23:53.302 --> 23:54.732
Local P.D. tossed it our way

23:54.733 --> 23:56.868
because it qualified as cult activity.

23:56.869 --> 24:00.071
So we stopped by the yogurt stand
to take a look.

24:00.072 --> 24:02.495
Within five minutes,
it's clear the whole thing is a front

24:02.520 --> 24:04.107
for a drug-dealing operation.

24:04.132 --> 24:06.044
We arrested Wayne in the back

24:06.045 --> 24:09.113
loading the cocaine
into little bags himself.

24:09.114 --> 24:12.044
He just gave us a look like,
"Oh, man."

24:12.069 --> 24:15.653
♪♪

24:15.654 --> 24:16.814
[Camera shutter clicks]

24:16.839 --> 24:18.623
So we figured, "Jackpot."

24:18.648 --> 24:19.965
We could use this interrogation

24:19.990 --> 24:22.711
to get inside the head of a cult leader.

24:22.736 --> 24:23.138
_

24:23.162 --> 24:26.998
Wayne, if it wasn't a spiritual journey,
what was it?

24:26.999 --> 24:30.402
I've just always really loved getting high.

24:32.771 --> 24:34.239
What about the women?

24:34.240 --> 24:38.540
Turns out they really love
getting high, too.

24:38.565 --> 24:40.923
He was always real fast with a quip.

24:40.948 --> 24:42.581
Yeah, I was jealous of it.

24:42.606 --> 24:45.516
- We're gonna have to clip your wings.
- No, no, I get it.

24:45.517 --> 24:49.053
Time to get this old boy
back on the reservation

24:49.054 --> 24:51.372
and let him play possum till the next time.

24:51.397 --> 24:55.094
Crazy Horse taps me on the shoulder
and says, "Let's ride."

24:57.229 --> 25:00.785
I don't really know what that means, but...

25:00.810 --> 25:02.800
how about we make a deal?

25:02.801 --> 25:04.612
♪♪

25:04.637 --> 25:07.471
That's a beautiful word, "deal"

25:07.496 --> 25:09.674
and you're talking to a dealer.

25:09.675 --> 25:11.442
♪♪

25:11.443 --> 25:15.142
Doss: So the three of us move into
an office, we start making a plan.

25:15.167 --> 25:18.037
I gotta say, that damn Wayne,

25:18.062 --> 25:19.918
he may have been half a kook,

25:19.943 --> 25:23.102
but, boy, when it came to cults,
he was smart as all get-out.

25:23.141 --> 25:25.014
_

25:25.039 --> 25:26.673
_

25:26.697 --> 25:28.593
_

25:28.641 --> 25:31.129
We asked him, "How do you get members?"

25:31.130 --> 25:34.722
He said we should take out
an ad with nonsense words on it.

25:34.747 --> 25:37.722
"Purify. Elevate. Liberate."

25:37.747 --> 25:41.072
People just started calling in
and started sending money for tapes.

25:41.073 --> 25:42.867
There is the world we see,

25:42.892 --> 25:47.211
but there's also a second world
that we do not.

25:47.212 --> 25:50.615
How do we unlock the door to that world?

25:50.616 --> 25:52.574
Who has the keys?

25:52.599 --> 25:53.828
Who lives there?

25:53.853 --> 25:55.860
What do they have for breakfast?

25:55.885 --> 25:57.355
He couldn't be Paternius anymore,

25:57.356 --> 25:59.716
so we had to come up with a new identity.

25:59.741 --> 26:02.260
Cooper was from Pittsburgh,
big Steelers fan.

26:02.261 --> 26:04.262
Cooper: Oh, yeah, man, I love the Steelers.

26:04.263 --> 26:05.997
Doss: Wayne suggests everyone in the cult

26:05.998 --> 26:08.661
should just be
the players names rearranged.

26:08.686 --> 26:11.369
Cooper: Bradshaw became Shawbard.

26:11.370 --> 26:15.341
Greene and Harris became Negree and Sharir.

26:15.366 --> 26:16.912
Father calls me Ra-Temblar.

26:16.937 --> 26:20.945
"Tem" is for the temple, and "blar" is
for the blaring of the message of love.

26:20.946 --> 26:22.682
I was named after God's kindness.

26:22.707 --> 26:24.363
Nope. You weren't named after kindness,

26:24.388 --> 26:26.317
you were named after Jack Lambert,

26:26.318 --> 26:29.973
meanest son of a bitch
to ever play the game.

26:29.998 --> 26:33.658
When God saw Jack Lambert play football,
he pissed his pants.

26:33.659 --> 26:37.261
Wayne even thought
everyone should wear Steeler colors.

26:37.262 --> 26:40.031
These people thought they were
on a path to enlightenment.

26:40.032 --> 26:44.635
And unbeknownst to them, they were dressed
like a bunch of drunks at a tailgate.

26:44.660 --> 26:46.785
[Laughs] We had a lot of fun.

26:46.810 --> 26:49.016
I don't think about it much
because of how it ended,

26:49.041 --> 26:51.275
but those were good times to be

26:51.276 --> 26:53.845
in the elite cult unit of the FBI.

26:53.846 --> 26:57.416
♪♪

27:01.620 --> 27:03.788
♪♪

27:03.789 --> 27:07.158
Doss: It's like sending
your kid off to college.

27:07.159 --> 27:12.897
We even loaned out a Rolls-Royce
from evidence for him to drive to Oregon.

27:12.898 --> 27:15.032
I remember patting on the hood
and telling him,

27:15.033 --> 27:16.901
"Screw who you want, do what you want,

27:16.902 --> 27:18.903
but stay off the drugs, Wayne."

27:18.904 --> 27:25.076
♪♪

27:25.077 --> 27:26.647
Everything got off to a great start.

27:26.679 --> 27:28.179
People were showing up every day,

27:28.180 --> 27:31.115
and they were totally
under Ra-Shawbard's control.

27:31.116 --> 27:34.185
So we started our experiment
to see how easily cult members

27:34.186 --> 27:37.455
would surrender
their free will to a leader.

27:37.456 --> 27:40.358
Cooper: These people ate up
everything Wayne told them to do.

27:40.359 --> 27:42.093
He had them talking to vegetables,

27:42.094 --> 27:45.410
dancing for hours on end,
spinning in circles.

27:45.435 --> 27:47.005
It was genius.

27:47.030 --> 27:49.711
But my favorite was Wayne's signature

27:49.736 --> 27:52.403
heliumtopic meditation.

27:52.404 --> 27:57.885
♪♪

27:57.910 --> 27:58.599
_

27:58.624 --> 28:00.789
Doss: Once a week,
members would suck on helium

28:00.814 --> 28:04.901
and then admit
what they were most ashamed of.

28:04.926 --> 28:07.652
[Helium hissing]

28:07.653 --> 28:10.521
[High-pitched voice] When I was 15...

28:10.522 --> 28:15.694
I stole my grandmother's locket
from my mother's jewelry drawer.

28:16.395 --> 28:22.468
I pawned it to get money
to go to Florida with my friends.

28:23.273 --> 28:25.169
Doss: After they confessed,
the rest of the group

28:25.194 --> 28:27.329
would wail on them with pool noodles.

28:27.354 --> 28:28.654
_

28:28.667 --> 28:34.145
♪♪

28:34.146 --> 28:36.147
And then finish up with a big old orgy

28:36.148 --> 28:39.224
with one great Wayne detail...

28:39.249 --> 28:41.805
they had to scream their orgasms into jars

28:41.830 --> 28:43.575
so that they could be saved.

28:43.600 --> 28:45.360
_

28:45.385 --> 28:49.594
[Men, women moaning pleasurably]

28:49.595 --> 28:54.232
He told us that we should save
our moments of ecstasy

28:54.233 --> 28:57.283
should there ever come a time
when darkness falls.

28:57.315 --> 28:59.570
♪♪

28:59.571 --> 29:01.005
It's a career case.

29:01.006 --> 29:03.139
I figured I might be in line
for deputy director,

29:03.164 --> 29:04.671
if not director one day.

29:04.696 --> 29:06.960
When we showed the world
what these cults were really about,

29:06.985 --> 29:10.015
who would ever join one again?

29:10.040 --> 29:11.690
Of course, we...

29:11.715 --> 29:14.070
we didn't count on Ra-Sharir.

29:14.095 --> 29:19.683
♪♪

29:19.708 --> 29:23.095
Ra-Sharir showed up after the first wave.

29:23.996 --> 29:26.840
[Laughs]

29:26.865 --> 29:28.975
And immediately engrained herself

29:29.000 --> 29:30.997
into Wayne's inner circle.

29:31.022 --> 29:34.138
Doss: Wayne told us she was
a true believer like he'd never seen.

29:34.139 --> 29:37.174
I told him, "Don't you ever let her forget
who's in charge."

29:37.175 --> 29:40.077
And, remember, stay off the drugs, Wayne."

29:40.078 --> 29:44.849
Cooper: He had a wicker chair, and
Ra-Sharir started calling it his throne.

29:44.850 --> 29:46.978
We should have seen that as a red flag.

29:47.003 --> 29:48.553
Doss: I didn't care about the throne.

29:48.554 --> 29:51.122
What I cared about is,
somehow this Ra-Sharir

29:51.123 --> 29:54.492
was becoming the spokesperson
for the cult that I started.

29:54.493 --> 29:56.961
When I read about the sign
in the grocery store,

29:56.962 --> 29:58.253
I was very upset.

29:58.278 --> 30:00.705
Then she goes
and she makes it a national news story

30:00.730 --> 30:03.134
by threatening to rename the town.

30:03.135 --> 30:06.618
Tonight, a small town in Oregon
may lose its name.

30:06.643 --> 30:08.372
Ra-Sharbarda.

30:08.373 --> 30:11.042
I reached out to Wayne,
I made it very clear,

30:11.043 --> 30:15.146
I said, "Wayne, you've gotta put
a stop to her."

30:15.147 --> 30:17.582
You're a little out of your lane, Wayne.

30:17.583 --> 30:22.217
Any chance you can pull
your friend Ra-Sharir back for us?

30:22.242 --> 30:24.021
Wayne: Who?

30:24.022 --> 30:25.114
Ra-Sharir, Wayne.

30:25.139 --> 30:27.487
The one who seems
to be running things over there.

30:27.512 --> 30:29.427
What? Ra-Sharir?

30:29.428 --> 30:30.995
Yeah, that's right... Ra-Sharir.

30:31.020 --> 30:32.265
Where?

30:32.290 --> 30:34.632
Oh, yeah, man.

30:34.633 --> 30:36.267
Ra-Sharir, she's...

30:36.268 --> 30:39.054
Yeah, she's... what a dynamite lady.

30:39.079 --> 30:41.021
Bill you gotta meet her.

30:41.046 --> 30:42.840
How the (bleep) am I gonna meet her, Wayne?

30:42.865 --> 30:45.181
I'm an FBI agent, and she's a cult member.

30:45.206 --> 30:46.490
Who is?

30:46.515 --> 30:48.594
Goddamn it. Ra-Sha...

30:48.619 --> 30:50.414
Wayne, are you back on drugs?

30:50.415 --> 30:53.427
That was our one rule, you son of a bitch!

30:53.452 --> 30:55.602
Whoa! Take it easy.

30:55.627 --> 30:57.126
Uncalled for.

30:57.151 --> 31:01.326
[Receiver clicks, dial tone]

31:03.228 --> 31:06.664
I always really regretted yelling at him.

31:06.665 --> 31:09.934
Especially since it was
the last time I ever spoke to him.

31:09.935 --> 31:12.036
News today out of
the Shawbard Valley Ranch,

31:12.037 --> 31:13.537
where Ra-Sharir has announced

31:13.538 --> 31:16.607
that Father Ra-Shawbard
has taken a vow of silence.

31:16.608 --> 31:19.910
Father will use his silence to contemplate

31:19.911 --> 31:22.136
what plagues this world.

31:22.922 --> 31:24.628
Doss: I saw him in that chair,

31:24.653 --> 31:27.802
and I realized we had to get him out.

31:27.827 --> 31:29.620
We made a plan.

31:29.621 --> 31:32.490
Larry would go in undercover
and extract Wayne.

31:32.491 --> 31:37.561
♪♪

31:37.562 --> 31:40.628
One day passes,
and I-I don't hear from Larry.

31:40.653 --> 31:43.467
Then two days, then three.

31:43.468 --> 31:45.660
Then on the fourth, I see him on the news,

31:45.685 --> 31:48.439
dancing with other cult members.

31:48.440 --> 31:53.124
♪♪

31:53.149 --> 31:56.881
Thinking, "Boy, Larry's really
going deep cover on this one."

31:56.882 --> 31:57.903
Then he calls.

31:57.928 --> 31:59.517
Cooper: Bill?

31:59.518 --> 32:02.535
Larry! Where the hell have you been?

32:02.560 --> 32:04.932
Uh, it's not Larry anymore.

32:04.957 --> 32:07.224
- My name is Ra-Tunbol.
- What?!

32:07.225 --> 32:10.526
I'm Ra-Tunbol now.
And I'm finally home.

32:10.551 --> 32:12.563
Ra-Tunbol?

32:12.564 --> 32:15.399
God! It's not Tunbol, it's Blount!

32:15.400 --> 32:18.469
He named you after
hall-of-fame cornerback Mel Blount!

32:18.470 --> 32:20.822
Be happy that the man
you once knew as Larry Cooper

32:20.854 --> 32:24.108
has found a peace he never knew
in the life he's leaving behind.

32:24.109 --> 32:25.742
You're not a cult member, Larry.

32:25.767 --> 32:27.783
Did you ever think
you might be a member of a cult?

32:27.808 --> 32:29.068
The cult of law enforcement?

32:29.093 --> 32:32.557
(Bleep) you, Larry!

32:32.582 --> 32:34.461
I did go in to extract Wayne.

32:34.486 --> 32:36.487
That was always the plan.

32:36.488 --> 32:40.524
But every time I talked
to a Shawbardite to get information,

32:40.525 --> 32:43.861
I left the conversation
feeling better about myself.

32:43.862 --> 32:47.791
I'd been divorced twice,
and my kids didn't talk to me.

32:47.823 --> 32:49.799
Maybe it's cause I drank too much back then

32:49.824 --> 32:51.335
or never called them.

32:51.336 --> 32:53.404
Maybe it's because I spent
too much damn time

32:53.405 --> 32:54.905
hanging out with serial killers.

32:54.906 --> 33:00.479
Point is, the Shawbardites taught me
to forgive myself.

33:01.313 --> 33:03.298
And once I did...

33:03.323 --> 33:05.516
I was happy.

33:05.517 --> 33:11.655
♪♪

33:11.656 --> 33:17.177
♪♪

33:17.202 --> 33:19.663
Well, I knew I had to go to the brass.

33:19.664 --> 33:21.989
_

33:22.014 --> 33:24.702
Jack Fancy was our section chief.

33:24.703 --> 33:27.513
Walking into his office,
thinking it couldn't be worse,

33:27.538 --> 33:29.870
and when I opened the door,

33:29.895 --> 33:31.885
he's watching Ra-Sharir on the news.

33:31.910 --> 33:35.076
This is an attack by the federal government

33:35.101 --> 33:37.348
on a religion of peace.

33:37.349 --> 33:40.818
Tonight, we bring you video
out of Shawbard Valley Ranch,

33:40.819 --> 33:44.255
but we warn you
what you're about to see is graphic.

33:44.256 --> 33:45.634
Ra-Sharir?

33:45.659 --> 33:47.269
Man: Oh, my God!

33:47.294 --> 33:49.300
So I'm watching this.

33:49.325 --> 33:51.570
Bill walks in, and I turn to him and say,

33:51.602 --> 33:55.132
"Do you notice that driver
looks a lot like Agent Cooper?"

33:55.133 --> 33:57.388
♪♪

33:57.413 --> 34:00.446
"By the way, where is Agent Cooper?"

34:00.471 --> 34:03.007
He just started to cry.

34:03.858 --> 34:06.052
Yeah, I cried.

34:06.077 --> 34:07.763
I cried hard.

34:07.803 --> 34:09.947
Cried for a real long time.

34:09.947 --> 34:13.819
♪♪

34:17.530 --> 34:21.358
♪♪

34:21.359 --> 34:23.194
Stratus: If you thought
things couldn't get worse

34:23.195 --> 34:26.864
for the people of the town formerly known
as Chinook, you'd be mistaken,

34:26.864 --> 34:30.887
as over half of the townspeople
now are infected with pink eye.

34:30.911 --> 34:33.003
Medical officials say
they've seen an influx

34:33.004 --> 34:34.951
of affected patients and are worried

34:34.976 --> 34:38.014
that they've got a full-scale epidemic
on their hands.

34:38.039 --> 34:40.025
In an effort to get to the bottom of why

34:40.050 --> 34:42.494
so may in our town have fallen ill,

34:42.518 --> 34:45.192
our local law enforcement
has pulled security video

34:45.217 --> 34:47.717
from all eating establishments.

34:47.719 --> 34:49.753
We do not think it is a coincidence

34:49.754 --> 34:54.924
that a town that has never had
this problem before is having it now...

34:54.949 --> 34:57.428
after a group of Shawbardites touched

34:57.429 --> 35:03.467
all the items in the salad bar
without even getting a salad.

35:03.468 --> 35:06.489
♪♪

35:06.514 --> 35:10.352
So if our friend Ra-Sharir is watching,

35:10.377 --> 35:13.611
I'd just like to say one thing...

35:13.612 --> 35:15.892
enough is enough.

35:15.917 --> 35:18.148
♪♪

35:18.149 --> 35:20.951
Doss: Turns out Ra-Sharir wasn't satisfied

35:20.952 --> 35:23.768
with giving conjunctivitis to Chinook.

35:23.793 --> 35:28.459
She was building a pink-eye army
to infiltrate all of Oregon.

35:28.460 --> 35:29.960
♪♪

35:29.961 --> 35:34.498
It was diabolical
because pink eye is so contagious.

35:34.499 --> 35:37.959
♪♪

35:37.984 --> 35:41.583
Around this time,
we got a hit on Ra-Sharir from Interpol.

35:41.608 --> 35:47.778
Her real name is Saavi Chambal,
and she was a known hypnotist.

35:47.779 --> 35:50.247
She was also wanted in five countries.

35:50.248 --> 35:52.917
Doss: Turned out, she had
a history of joining cults

35:52.918 --> 35:56.353
with the suspected goal
of convincing everyone to go off themselves

35:56.354 --> 35:58.122
so she could get away with the money.

35:58.123 --> 36:02.159
We even found some photos that led us
to believe she was at Jonestown.

36:02.160 --> 36:04.061
♪♪

36:04.062 --> 36:07.280
That was all we needed
to surround the ranch.

36:07.305 --> 36:08.908
[Siren wailing]

36:08.933 --> 36:11.255
_

36:11.280 --> 36:12.870
Woman: Tensions are running high here

36:12.871 --> 36:14.772
outside of Shawbard Valley Ranch,

36:14.773 --> 36:16.974
where federal agents
have surrounded the area.

36:16.975 --> 36:18.611
Man: The path to Shawbard Valley Ranch

36:18.636 --> 36:22.212
has been completely blocked
by a barricade of Mason jars.

36:22.213 --> 36:24.605
And what's in these jars is anyone's guess,

36:24.630 --> 36:27.239
but it could be noxious gases.

36:27.264 --> 36:29.920
Fancy: There was a theory
that we were dealing with chemical warfare.

36:29.921 --> 36:32.756
I called Agent Doss to see what he thought.

36:32.757 --> 36:34.992
Doss: I told Agent Fancy
it was probably the jars

36:34.993 --> 36:37.728
they screamed their orgasms into.

36:37.729 --> 36:39.263
Then he hung up on me.

36:39.264 --> 36:43.067
The hope was that the joy
of the orgasm jars...

36:43.068 --> 36:47.204
would turn back the violent urges
of the law enforcement.

36:47.205 --> 36:52.425
♪♪

36:52.450 --> 36:54.545
It did not.

36:54.546 --> 36:59.883
♪♪

36:59.884 --> 37:05.007
♪♪

37:05.032 --> 37:07.124
Ra-Sharir: They are coming for us.

37:07.125 --> 37:09.428
You can hear them getting closer.

37:09.453 --> 37:12.029
-Shh.
Doss: - Sick to my stomach.

37:12.030 --> 37:14.898
I knew the power Ra-Sharir
had over those people,

37:14.899 --> 37:16.919
and now I knew what she was planning to do.

37:16.944 --> 37:18.776
But they do not know

37:18.801 --> 37:21.514
that we have a better life waiting for us

37:21.539 --> 37:23.474
after this one, huh?!

37:23.475 --> 37:26.110
Our fear was
that she would give a suicide order,

37:26.111 --> 37:27.706
and that's exactly what she did.

37:27.731 --> 37:32.649
So tell me, are you ready
to die today, huh?

37:32.650 --> 37:35.678
I thought I was going to have
the blood of 200 people on my hands.

37:35.703 --> 37:39.958
I said, are you ready to die today?!

37:41.235 --> 37:42.821
Man: Um, no.

37:42.846 --> 37:45.129
What? Who said that?

37:45.130 --> 37:48.090
I just don't think, like, in general,

37:48.115 --> 37:51.368
that's what we're here for.

37:51.369 --> 37:55.061
Are you not here
to follow Father Ra-Shawbard?

37:55.086 --> 37:57.490
We are, but, like, where is he?

37:57.515 --> 38:01.178
He is recovering, and I speak for him.

38:01.179 --> 38:04.314
If I may, I think
what we're all reacting to

38:04.315 --> 38:09.027
is how aggressive things have gotten here.

38:09.052 --> 38:12.083
A month ago, this place
had a really good vibe.

38:12.108 --> 38:14.463
Now, there's, like, guns everywhere

38:14.488 --> 38:16.475
and itchy eyes.

38:16.500 --> 38:20.330
And there are hardly any orgies.

38:20.331 --> 38:24.642
And it's just not
what we all signed up for.

38:24.667 --> 38:26.136
Everyone look at me!

38:26.137 --> 38:27.571
Here's the thing...

38:27.572 --> 38:32.393
the eyes are the most important tool
a hypnotist has.

38:32.418 --> 38:34.091
A hypnotist with pink eye

38:34.116 --> 38:36.847
is like a boxer with two broken hands.

38:36.848 --> 38:40.884
♪♪

38:40.885 --> 38:44.955
Look at me-e-e-e.

38:44.956 --> 38:47.764
Doss: Thank God for pink eye.

38:47.789 --> 38:49.493
Fancy: In a standoff situation,

38:49.494 --> 38:52.875
the dream is everyone comes out
with their hands up.

38:52.900 --> 38:54.883
This was that dream.

38:54.908 --> 38:56.318
[Helicopter blades whirring]

38:56.343 --> 38:57.543
_

38:57.590 --> 39:00.613
Reporter: The siege at Shawbard Valley
Ranch is over before it started,

39:00.638 --> 39:03.607
with members turning themselves in
to federal agents.

39:03.608 --> 39:05.843
Most were released
within the course of a day,

39:05.844 --> 39:10.080
save for one, Ra-Sharir,
who is in police custody.

39:10.081 --> 39:14.152
♪♪

39:14.200 --> 39:16.386
Doss: We had multiple witnesses
who corroborated

39:16.387 --> 39:19.256
that Ra-Sharir had tried
to pink eye the entire state.

39:19.257 --> 39:21.556
We could have put her away for years.

39:21.581 --> 39:23.944
But she had an ace up her sleeve.

39:23.969 --> 39:25.395
I simply played them a tape

39:25.396 --> 39:27.807
that I thought they might find interesting.

39:27.832 --> 39:29.700
[Reel whirs]

39:29.701 --> 39:32.170
[Helium hissing]

39:33.538 --> 39:35.719
[High-pitched voice] I'm an FBI agent.

39:35.744 --> 39:40.077
My partner and I recruited a man
named Wayne Delancey to start this cult

39:40.078 --> 39:42.580
and then run it to our specifications.

39:44.949 --> 39:46.450
[Inhales sharply]

39:46.451 --> 39:48.852
[Helium hissing]

39:48.853 --> 39:53.257
The U.S. government is responsible
for everything that has happened here.

39:53.258 --> 39:55.626
[Normal voice] I'm sorry.

39:55.627 --> 39:57.294
[Sobbing]

39:57.319 --> 40:01.883
I cannot speak to why she was released,
but she was released.

40:01.908 --> 40:04.612
Today, the final member
of the Shawbard Valley Ranch

40:04.637 --> 40:06.333
was released from federal custody,

40:06.358 --> 40:09.139
and Ra-Sharir had a message for everyone.

40:09.140 --> 40:11.667
You want to know what I think?

40:11.692 --> 40:14.111
Tough titties!

40:14.112 --> 40:15.613
[All shouting]

40:19.717 --> 40:24.729
♪♪

40:24.754 --> 40:26.952
Cooper: I took my pension
and never looked back.

40:26.977 --> 40:30.594
I spent the next few years
getting in touch with my kids.

40:30.595 --> 40:34.309
It's not perfect,
but three out of four of them call me Dad.

40:34.334 --> 40:37.173
I kicked around, did some odd jobs.

40:37.198 --> 40:40.252
But something was still missing for me.

40:40.277 --> 40:42.625
And so I went out and found it.

40:42.650 --> 40:48.011
♪♪

40:48.012 --> 40:52.549
♪♪

40:52.550 --> 40:55.661
I think the thing about me
that surprises people the most

40:55.686 --> 40:57.816
is that I stayed in Chinook.

40:57.841 --> 40:59.094
[Chuckles]

40:59.119 --> 41:02.165
The reality was, despite how it ended,

41:02.190 --> 41:04.792
I'd enjoyed my time here.

41:04.817 --> 41:05.919
Mm.

41:05.944 --> 41:08.769
Man: I mean, sure, it was weird at first.

41:08.794 --> 41:10.833
But you get used to things.

41:10.858 --> 41:13.817
Plus, she makes a hell of a green juice.

41:13.842 --> 41:16.095
Well, sure, I'm surprised we're friends.

41:16.120 --> 41:17.631
But what can I say?

41:17.656 --> 41:21.615
My God teaches me to forgive.

41:21.640 --> 41:23.580
That doesn't mean I forget.

41:23.581 --> 41:27.229
Every day when I go to pay
for my juice...

41:27.254 --> 41:29.419
I do it in pennies.

41:29.420 --> 41:36.483
♪♪

41:36.530 --> 41:38.665
Fancy: What do I think happened
to Wayne Delancey?

41:38.690 --> 41:40.564
He's probably dead.

41:40.565 --> 41:43.546
Agents on the scene
searched Shawbard's domicile

41:43.571 --> 41:45.335
but couldn't find him.

41:45.336 --> 41:47.337
Based on his injuries from the car accident

41:47.338 --> 41:49.072
and the fact that he never saw a doctor,

41:49.073 --> 41:53.500
our best guess, he's buried
on the premises somewhere.

41:53.525 --> 41:55.312
If I ask you to picture Wayne Delancey

41:55.313 --> 41:56.546
with his beard shaved off,

41:56.547 --> 42:00.550
wearing an FBI jacket and sunglasses,

42:00.551 --> 42:04.046
you think it would look anything like this?

42:04.071 --> 42:06.575
And if he is dead,
do you want to explain to me

42:06.600 --> 42:09.679
why every year
on the anniversary of the raid,

42:09.704 --> 42:11.395
I get a Pittsburgh Steelers postcard

42:11.396 --> 42:13.830
sent from a different corner of the globe?

42:13.831 --> 42:15.532
♪♪

42:15.533 --> 42:17.875
When people find out I'm a Shawbardite,

42:17.900 --> 42:20.240
they are surprised that I still adhere

42:20.265 --> 42:22.239
to the teachings of a con man

42:22.240 --> 42:25.286
who was only pretending
to be a spiritual leader.

42:25.311 --> 42:31.477
And the only thing I can tell them is
that I was sad before I met him...

42:31.502 --> 42:34.635
and happy when I knew him.

42:34.660 --> 42:38.488
And I don't know what more
to want from anyone other than that.

42:38.489 --> 42:40.475
♪♪

42:40.500 --> 42:43.527
I do wish he hadn't stolen from me, though.

42:43.528 --> 42:51.501
♪♪

42:51.502 --> 42:59.609
♪♪

42:59.610 --> 43:04.481
♪♪

43:04.482 --> 43:06.983
[Birds chirping]

43:06.984 --> 43:16.294
Sync and corrections FunnyFunk
